{"_id": "32693241|None", "id": "32693241", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Life Sci.; 2020 Jul 18 118114. doi:10.1016/j.lfs.2020.118114", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Paniri A, Akhavan-Niaki H, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Emerging role of IL-6 and NLRP3 inflammasome as potential therapeutic targets to combat COVID-19: Role of lncRNAs in cytokine storm modulation.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "3569", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "502"}, "text": "IL-6", "locations": [{"offset": 17, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "114548", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3600"}, "text": "NLRP3", "locations": [{"offset": 26, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 88, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 144, "text": "The world has witnessed a high morbidity and mortality caused by SARS-CoV-2, and global death toll is still rising. Exaggerated inflammatory responses are thought to be more responsible for infiltrated immune cells accumulation, organ damage especially lung, dyspnea, and respiratory failure rather than direct effect of viral replication. IL-6 and NLRP3 inflammasome are the major immune components in immune responses stimulation upon pathogen infection. It's noteworthy that the function and expression of these components are remarkably influenced by non-coding RNAs including long non-coding RNAs. Given the potential role of these components in organ damage and pathological manifestations of patients infected with COVID-19, their blockage might be a hopeful and promising treatment strategy. Notably, more study on long non-coding RNAs involved in inflammatory responses could elevate the efficacy of anti-inflammatory therapy. In this review we discuss the potential impact of IL-6 and NLRP3 inflammasome blocker drugs on inflammatory responses, viral clearance, and pathological and clinical manifestations. Collectively, anti-inflammatory strategy might pave the way to diminish clinical and pathological manifestations and thereby discharging patients infected with COVID-19 from hospital.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "mortality", "locations": [{"offset": 189, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 209, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "death", "locations": [{"offset": 232, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019965", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "organ damage", "locations": [{"offset": 373, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D004417", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "dyspnea", "locations": [{"offset": 403, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012131", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "respiratory failure", "locations": [{"offset": 416, "length": 19}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "3569", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "502"}, "text": "IL-6", "locations": [{"offset": 484, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "114548", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3600"}, "text": "NLRP3", "locations": [{"offset": 493, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 590, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019965", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "organ damage", "locations": [{"offset": 795, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 843, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infected", "locations": [{"offset": 852, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 866, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "3569", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "502"}, "text": "IL-6", "locations": [{"offset": 1130, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "114548", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3600"}, "text": "NLRP3", "locations": [{"offset": 1139, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1399, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "40", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infected", "locations": [{"offset": 1408, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "41", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1422, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32693241, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["gene@3569", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D003643", "disease@MESH:D012131", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:D004417", "gene@114548", "species@2697049", "disease@MESH:D007239", "disease@MESH:D019965"], "journal": "Life Sci.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Paniri A", "Akhavan-Niaki H"]}
{"_id": "32693224|None", "id": "32693224", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "World Neurosurg; 2020 Jul 18 . doi:10.1016/j.wneu.2020.07.080", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Fernandes Cabral DT, Alan N, Agarwal N, Lunsford D, Monaco EA, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "COVID-19 and Neurosurgery Residency Action Plan: An Institutional Experience from the United States of America.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 112, "text": "BACKGROUND: The current pandemic crisis caused by a novel human coronavirus, named severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV2), has forced a dramatic change in our society. A key portion of the medical work force on the front line is comprised of resident physicians. Thus, it becomes imperative to create an adequate and effective action plan to restructure this valuable human resource amid the SARS-CoV2 pandemic. OBJECTIVE: To describe a comprehensive approach taken by a Neurosurgery Department in quaternary care academic institution in the United States of America amid the SARS-CoV2 pandemic focused in resident training and support. INTERVENTIONS: A restructuring of the Neurosurgery Department at our academic institution was performed focused on decreasing their risk of infection/exposure and transmission to others, while minimizing negative consequences in the training experience. An on-line academic platform was built for: resident education, guidance, and support, as well as continue channel for pandemic update by the department leadership. CONCLUSIONS: and Relevance: The SARS-CoV2 pandemic constitutes a global health emergency full of uncertainty. Treatment, scope, duration, and economic burden forced a major restructuring of our medical practice. In this regard, academic institutions must direct efforts to diminish further negative impact in the training and education of the upcoming generation of physicians including those currently in medical school. Perhaps the only silver lining in this terrible disruption will be greater appreciation of the role of current health care providers and educators, whose contributions to our society are often neglected or unrecognized.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "10", "infons": {"identifier": "694448", "type": "Species"}, "text": "human coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 170, "length": 17}]}, {"id": "11", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2", "locations": [{"offset": 195, "length": 47}]}, {"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV2", "locations": [{"offset": 244, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 501, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV2", "locations": [{"offset": 525, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV2", "locations": [{"offset": 709, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 910, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV2", "locations": [{"offset": 1221, "length": 9}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32693224, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "species@694448", "species@2697049", "disease@MESH:D007239"], "journal": "World Neurosurg", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Fernandes Cabral DT", "Alan N", "Agarwal N", "Lunsford D", "Monaco EA"]}
