{"_id": "32693151|None", "id": "32693151", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Int J Surg; 2020 Jul 18 . doi:10.1016/j.ijsu.2020.07.023", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Philouze P, Cortet M, Quatrone D, C\u00e9ruse P, Aubrun F, Dubernard G, Mabrut JY, Delignette MC, Mohkam K, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Surgical activity during the Covid-19 pandemic: results for 112 patients in a French tertiary care center, a quality improvement study.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 29, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 64, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 136, "text": "BACKGROUND: After the emergence of Covid-19 in China, Hubei Province, the epidemic quickly spread to Europe. France was quickly hit and our institution was one of the first French university to receive patients infected with Sars-COV2. The predicted massive influx of patients motivated the cancellation of all elective surgical procedures planned to free hospitalization beds and to free intensive care beds. Nevertheless, we should properly select patients who will be canceled to avoid life-threatening. The retained surgical indications are surgical emergencies, oncologic surgery, and organ transplantation. MATERIAL AND METHODS: We describe the organization of our institution which allows the continuation of these surgical activities while limiting the exposure of our patients to the Sars Cov2. RESULTS: After 4 weeks of implementation of intra-hospital protocols for the control of the Covid-19 epidemic, 112 patients were operated on (104 oncology or emergency surgeries and 8 liver transplants). Only one case of post-operative contamination was observed. No mortality related to Covid-19 was noted. No cases of contamination of surgical care personnel have been reported. CONCLUSION: We found that the performance of oncological or emergency surgery is possible, safe for both patients and caregivers.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 171, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 338, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infected", "locations": [{"offset": 347, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Sars-COV2", "locations": [{"offset": 361, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 404, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 586, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 913, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Sars Cov2", "locations": [{"offset": 929, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1032, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1055, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1228, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1426, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32693151, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D007239", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "species@2697049"], "journal": "Int J Surg", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Philouze P", "Cortet M", "Quatrone D", "C\u00e9ruse P", "Aubrun F", "Dubernard G", "Mabrut JY", "Delignette MC", "Mohkam K"]}
{"_id": "32693122|None", "id": "32693122", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Int. J. Biol. Macromol.; 2020 Jul 18 . doi:10.1016/j.ijbiomac.2020.07.174", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Souza PFN, Lopes FES, Amaral JL, Freitas CDT, Oliveira JTA, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "A molecular docking study revealed that synthetic peptides induced conformational changes in the structure of SARS-CoV-2 spike glycoprotein, disrupting the interaction with human ACE2 receptor.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D010455", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "peptides", "locations": [{"offset": 50, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 110, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 173, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "59272", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "41448"}, "text": "ACE2", "locations": [{"offset": 179, "length": 4}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 194, "text": "The global outbreak of COVID-19 (Coronavirus Disease 2019) caused by SARS-CoV-2 (Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome caused by Coronavirus 2) began in December 2019. Its closest relative, SARS-CoV-1, has a slightly mutated Spike (S) protein, which interacts with ACE2 receptor in human cells to start the infection. So far, there are no vaccines or drugs to treat COVID-19. So, research groups worldwide are seeking new molecules targeting the S protein to prevent infection by SARS-CoV-2 and COVID-19 establishment. We performed molecular docking analysis of eight synthetic peptides against SARS-CoV-2 S protein. All interacted with the protein, but Mo-CBP3-PepII and PepKAA had the highest affinity with it. By binding to the S protein, both peptides led to conformational alterations in the protein, resulting in incorrect interaction with ACE2. Therefore, given the importance of the S protein-ACE2 interaction for SARS-CoV-2 infection, synthetic peptides could block SARS-CoV-2 infection. Moreover, unlike other antiviral drugs, peptides have no toxicity to human cells. Thus, these peptides are potential molecules to be tested against SARS-CoV-2 and to develop new drugs to treat COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Coronavirus Disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 227, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 263, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012120", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Respiratory Syndrome", "locations": [{"offset": 288, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Coronavirus 2", "locations": [{"offset": 319, "length": 13}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "694009", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV", "locations": [{"offset": 380, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 472, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 497, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 556, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 657, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 670, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 685, "length": 8}]}, {"