{"_id": "32692903|None", "id": "32692903", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Obesity (Silver Spring); 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1002/oby.22976", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Kow CS, Hasan SS, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "The potential benefit of telmisartan to protect overweight COPD patients from the acquisition of COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D000077333", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "telmisartan", "locations": [{"offset": 25, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D029424", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COPD", "locations": [{"offset": 59, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 64, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 97, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 107, "text": "Individuals with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) have long been identified to have an elevated serum level of angiotensin-converting enzyme 2 (ACE2), the cellular entry receptor for severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2). The newest discoveries by Higham et al. (1) were the increased ACE2 expression in the bronchial epithelium of overweight COPD patients compared to their non-overweight counterparts.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D029424", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "chronic obstructive pulmonary disease", "locations": [{"offset": 124, "length": 37}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D029424", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COPD", "locations": [{"offset": 163, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "59272", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "41448"}, "text": "angiotensin-converting enzyme 2", "locations": [{"offset": 23