{"_id": "32692894|None", "id": "32692894", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Thromb. Haemost.; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1111/jth.15021", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Macci\u00f2 A, Madeddu C, Caocci G, La Nasa G, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Multifactorial pathogenesis of COVID-19-related coagulopathy. Can defibrotide have a role in the early phases of coagulation disorders?", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 31, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001778", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coagulopathy", "locations": [{"offset": 48, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C036901", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "defibrotide", "locations": [{"offset": 66, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001778", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coagulation disorders", "locations": [{"offset": 113, "length": 21}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 136, "text": "Thrombotic complications emerged as an important issue in patients with coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19). Consolidated reports regarding the clinical and laboratory findings in COVID-19 patients reveal thrombocytopenia, elevated D-dimer, prolonged prothrombin time, disseminated intravascular coagulation, and pulmonary intravascular coagulation (PIC). Recently, some authors emphasized the potential role of antiphospholipid antibodies in the pathogenesis of thrombotic events in patients with severe COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013927", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Thrombotic complications", "locations": [{"offset": 136, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 194, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coronavirus disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 208, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 234, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 316, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 325, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013921", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "thrombocytopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 341, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D004211", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "intravascular coagulation", "locations": [{"offset": 418, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D004211", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "pulmonary intravascular coagulation", "locations": [{"offset": 449, "length": 35}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013927", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "thrombotic", "locations": [{"offset": 599, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 620, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 641, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692894, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["chemical@MESH:C036901", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D013921", "disease@MESH:D004211", "disease@MESH:D013927", "disease@MESH:D001778"], "journal": "J. Thromb. Haemost.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Macci\u00f2 A", "Madeddu C", "Caocci G", "La Nasa G"]}
{"_id": "32692890|None", "id": "32692890", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Med Anthropol Q; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1111/maq.12599", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Caduff C, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "What Went Wrong: Corona and the World after the Full Stop.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 59, "text": "This article examines the global response to the Covid-19 pandemic. It argues that we urgently need to look beyond the virus if we want to understand the real seriousness of what is happening today. How did we end up in a space of thinking, acting, and feeling that has normalized extremes and is based on the assumption that biological life is an absolute value separate from politics? The author suggests that today's fear is fueled by mathematical disease modeling, neoliberal health policies, nervous media reporting, and authoritarian longings.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 108, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692890, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "Med Anthropol Q", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Caduff C"]}
{"_id": "32692877|None", "id": "32692877", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Thromb. Haemost.; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1111/jth.15017", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Keragala CB, Medcalf RL, Myles PS, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Fibrinolysis and COVID-19: a tale of two sites?", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 17, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 48, "text": "We thank Tang et al. for their perspective on the possible limitation of D-dimer levels guiding anticoagulant treatment in patients with COVID-19 [1]. Although there is a clear association with elevated D-dimer and severity of COVID-19 disease, it is important to highlight the fact that D-dimer has always been utilised in conjunction with clinical pre-test probability, as a predictive tool to help exclude a possible diagnosis of venous thromboembolism. It has never been validated to guide clinical treatment or anticoagulation. It has recently been noted that a significant proportion of the recent literature concerning D-dimer in COVID-19 is fraught with variable, poor or incomplete reporting which further muddies its role in the management of COVID-19 related coagulopathy[2].", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "9", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 171, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "10", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 185, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "11", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 275, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D054556", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "venous thromboembolism", "locations": [{"offset": 481, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 685, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 801, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001778", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coagulopathy", "locations": [{"offset": 818, "length": 12}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692877, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@9606", "disease@MESH:D001778", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D054556"], "journal": "J. Thromb. Haemost.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Keragala CB", "Medcalf RL", "Myles PS"]}
{"_id": "32692874|None", "id": "32692874", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Thromb. Haemost.; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1111/jth.15022", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Pesavento R, Ceccato D, Pasquetto G, Monticelli J, Leone L, Frigo A, Gorgi D, Postal A, Marchese GM, Cipriani A, Saller A, Sarais C, Criveller P, Gemelli M, Capone F, Fioretto P, Pagano C, Rossato M, Avogaro A, Simioni P, Prandoni P, Vettor R, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "The hazard of (sub)therapeutic doses of anticoagulants in non-critically ill patients with Covid-19: the Padua province experience.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D016638", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "critically ill", "locations": [{"offset": 62, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 77, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 91, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 132, "text": "BACKGROUND: COVID-19 is responsible for a worldwide pandemic, with a high rate of morbidity and mortality. The increasing evidence of an associated relevant pro-thrombotic coagulopathy has resulted in an increasing use of antithrombotic doses higher than usual in COVID-19 patients. Information on the benefit/risk ratio of this approach is still lacking. OBJECTIVE: to assess the incidence of relevant bleeding complications in association with the antithrombotic strategy, and its relationship with the amount of drug. METHODS: Consecutive COVID-19 patients admitted between February and April 2020 were included in a retrospective analysis. Major bleedings (MB) and clinical relevant non-major bleeding (CRNMB) were obtained from patient medical records and were adjudicated by an independent committee. RESULTS: Of the 324 patients who were recruited, 240 had been treated with prophylactic doses and 84 with higher doses of anticoagulants. The rate of the composite endpoint of MB or CRNMB was 6.9 per 100 person/months in patients who had been given prophylactic doses, and 26.4 per 100 persons/months in those who had been prescribed higher doses (HR 3.89; 95%CI, 1.90 to 7.97). The corresponding rates for overall mortality were 12.2 and 20.1 per 100 person/months, respectively. CONCLUSIONS: The rate of relevant bleeding events were high in patients treated with (sub)therapeutic doses of anticoagulants. In the latter group, overall mortality did not differ from that of patients treated with standard prophylactic doses and was even higher. Our result does not support a strategy of giving (sub)therapeutic doses of anticoagulants in non-critically ill patients with COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 144, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "mortality", "locations": [{"offset": 228, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013927", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "thrombotic coagulopathy", "locations": [{"offset": 293, "length": 23}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 396, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 405, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006470", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "bleeding complications", "locations": [{"offset": 535, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 674, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 683, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "OMIM:613675", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "MB", "locations": [{"offset": 793, "length": 2}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006470", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "bleeding", "locations": [{"offset": 829, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 865, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "40", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 959, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "41", "infons": {"identifier": "OMIM:613675", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "MB", "locations": [{"offset": 1115, "length": 2}]}, {"id": "42", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1160, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "43", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "persons", "locations": [{"offset": 1225, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "44", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "mortality", "locations": [{"offset": 1354, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "45", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006470", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "bleeding", "locations": [{"offset": 1454, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "46", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1483, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "47", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "mortality", "locations": [{"offset": 1576, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "48", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1614, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "49", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D016638", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "critically ill", "locations": [{"offset": 1782, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "50", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1797, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "51", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1811, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692874, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D016638", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:D003643", "disease@OMIM:613675", "disease@MESH:D013927", "disease@MESH:D006470"], "journal": "J. Thromb. Haemost.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Pesavento R", "Ceccato D", "Pasquetto G", "Monticelli J", "Leone L", "Frigo A", "Gorgi D", "Postal A", "Marchese GM", "Cipriani A", "Saller A", "Sarais C", "Criveller P", "Gemelli M", "Capone F", "Fioretto P", "Pagano C", "Rossato M", "Avogaro A", "Simioni P", "Prandoni P", "Vettor R"]}
{"_id": "32692867|None", "id": "32692867", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Fam Process; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1111/famp.12589", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Burgoyne N, Cohn AS, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Lessons from the Transition to Relational Teletherapy During COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 61, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 71, "text": "When the World Health Organization declared the coronavirus outbreak a pandemic, clinicians were challenged to maintain continuity of care. Teletherapy became the primary means of service delivery for many who had never or only sparingly used it. The Family Institute at Northwestern University, in response to encouraging findings with respect to the effectiveness of teletherapy and recognizing advantages with respect to access to care, launched our teletherapy services in 2018. As a relationship-based organization, we were keen to exploit the opportunity that teletherapy provides to integrate additional members of the client system into the treatment. Over these two plus years we have learned a great deal. Our learning was greatly accelerated by our transition to a 100% teletherapy practice in the wake of the pandemic. Teletherapy is a different context. Intentionally managing the context's constraints and exploiting its strengths is key to providing high quality couple and family therapy. This step is often overlooked or resisted when teletherapy is an occasional add-on to a face-to-face practice.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "11118", "type": "Species"}, "text": "coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 119, "length": 11}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692867, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@11118", "disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "Fam Process", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Burgoyne N", "Cohn AS"]}
{"_id": "32692862|None", "id": "32692862", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Thromb. Haemost.; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1111/jth.15018", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Patell R, Bogue T, Bindal P, Koshy A, Merrill M, Aird WC, Bauer KA, Zwicker JI, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Incidence of thrombosis and hemorrhage in hospitalized cancer patients with COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013927", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "thrombosis", "locations": [{"offset": 13, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006470", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "hemorrhage", "locations": [{"offset": 28, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "cancer", "locations": [{"offset": 55, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "8", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 62, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "9", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 76, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 86, "text": "BACKGROUND: Coronavirus Disease-2019 (COVID-19) is a recognized prothrombotic state. Patients hospitalized with active cancer are predisposed to thrombosis but whether active cancer further amplifies thrombotic risk with COVID-19 is not known. OBJECTIVES: To evaluate cumulative incidences of thrombotic and hemorrhagic events in hospitalized COVID-19 patients with and without active cancer at 28 days. METHODS: A retrospective cohort analyses of consecutive adults hospitalized with COVID-19 was performed. Active cancer required cancer-directed therapy within last 6 months. The cumulative incidences of thrombosis or hemorrhage were estimated considering death as a competing risk. RESULTS: Patients without cancer (n=353) and active cancer (n=45) were comparable in terms of age, sex, antibiotics administered, length of hospitalization, and critical care. The most common malignancies were lymphoid (17.8%), gastrointestinal (15.6%), lung (13.3%), and genitourinary (13.3%). At day 28, the cumulative incidence of thrombotic events was 18.2% (95% CI, 10.2% to 27.9%) in non-cancer cohort and 14.2% (95% CI, 4.7% to 28.7%) in the cancer cohort. The cumulative incidence of major and fatal bleeding at day 28 was 20.8% (95% CI, 12.1 to 31.0%) in the non-cancer group and 19.5% (95% CI, 5.5% to 39.8%) in the cancer cohort. Three patients experienced fatal bleeds, all of whom were in the non-cancer cohort. Survival was significantly shorter in the group with active cancer (P=0.038). CONCLUSIONS: We observed a similarly high incidence of thrombosis and bleeding among patients admitted with COVID-19 with or without active cancer.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "48", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Coronavirus Disease-2019", "locations": [{"offset": 98, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "49", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 124, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "50", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Patients", "locations": [{"offset": 171, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "51", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "cancer", "locations": [{"offset": 205, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "52", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013927", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "thrombosis", "locations": [{"offset": 231, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "53", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "cancer", "locations": [{"offset": 261, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "54", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013927", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "thrombotic", "locations": [{"offset": 286, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "55", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "lo