{"_id": "32692726|None", "id": "32692726", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Clin. Invest.; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1172/JCI142151", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Gulick RM, Sobieszczyk ME, Landry DW, Hollenberg AN, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Prioritizing clinical research studies during the COVID-19 pandemic: lessons from New York City.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 50, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 97, "text": "A retrospective look at how clinical research trials were prioritized in New York City in the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic provides insights for future clinical research efforts.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 203, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692726, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "J. Clin. Invest.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Gulick RM", "Sobieszczyk ME", "Landry DW", "Hollenberg AN"]}
{"_id": "32692724|None", "id": "32692724", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Aging (Albany NY); 2020 Jul 21 ; 12. doi:10.18632/aging.103687", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Munayco C, Chowell G, Tariq A, Undurraga EA, Mizumoto K, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Risk of death by age and gender from CoVID-19 in Peru, March-May, 2020.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "death", "locations": [{"offset": 8, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "CoVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 37, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 72, "text": "Peru implemented strict social distancing measures during the early phase of the epidemic and is now experiencing one of the largest CoVID-19 epidemics in Latin America. Estimates of disease severity are an essential indicator to inform policy decisions about the intensity and duration of interventions needed to mitigate the outbreak. Here we derive delay-adjusted case fatality risks (aCFR) of CoVID-19 in a middle-income country in South America.We utilize government-reported time series of CoVID-19 cases and deaths in Peru stratified by age group and gender.As of May 25, 2020, we estimate the aCFR for men and women at 10.8% (95%CrI: 10.5-11.1%) and 6.5% (95%CrI: 6.2-6.8%), respectively, whereas the overall aCFR was estimated at 9.1% (95%CrI: 8.9-9.3%). Our results show that senior individuals have been the most severely affected by CoVID-19, particularly men, with an aCFR of nearly 60% for those aged 80- years. We also found that men have a significantly higher cumulative morbidity ratio across most age groups (proportion test, p-value< 0.001), with the exception of those aged 0-9 years.The ongoing CoVID-19 pandemic is generating a substantial mortality burden in Peru. Senior individuals, especially those older than 70 years, are being disproportionately affected by the CoVID-19 pandemic.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "CoVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 205, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "CoVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 469, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "CoVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 568, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "deaths", "locations": [{"offset": 587, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "men", "locations": [{"offset": 682, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 690, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "CoVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 917, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "men", "locations": [{"offset": 940, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "men", "locations": [{"offset": 1017, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "CoVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1189, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "mortality", "locations": [{"offset": 1235, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "CoVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1364, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692724, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D003643"], "journal": "Aging (Albany 