{"_id": "32692408|None", "id": "32692408", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Histopathology; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1111/his.14215", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Smithgall MC, Liu-Jarin X, Hamele-Bena D, Cimic A, Mourad M, Debelenko L, Chen X, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Third Trimester Placentas of SARS-CoV-2-Positive Women: Histomorphology, including Viral Immunohistochemistry and in Situ Hybridization.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 29, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Women", "locations": [{"offset": 49, "length": 5}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 137, "text": "AIMS: The wide-variety of affected organ-systems associated with SARS-CoV-2 infection highlights the need for tissue-specific evaluation. We compared placentas from SARS-CoV-2-positive and negative women in our hospital in New York City, which became the epicenter of the COVID-19 pandemic in March 2020. While some limited studies have been published on placentas from SARS-CoV-2-positive women to date, this study, in addition to describing histomorphology, utilizes in-situ hybridization (ISH) for the S-gene encoding the spike-protein and immunohistochemistry (IHC) with the monoclonal-SARS-CoV-2 spike-antibody 1A9 for placental evaluation. METHODS AND RESULTS: In this study, 51 singleton, third-trimester placentas from SARS-CoV-2-positive women and 25 singleton, third-trimester placentas from SARS-CoV-2-negative women were examined histomorphologically using the Amsterdam Criteria as well as with ISH and/or IHC. Corresponding clinical findings and neonatal outcomes also were recorded. While no specific histomorphologic changes related to SARS-CoV-2 were noted in the placentas, evidence of maternal/fetal vascular malperfusion was identified, with placentas from SARS-CoV-2-positive women significantly more likely to show villous agglutination (p=0.003) and subchorionic thrombi (p=0.026) than placentas from SARS-CoV-2-negative women. No evidence of direct viral involvement was identified using ISH and IHC. CONCLUSIONS: In this study, third trimester placentas from SARS-CoV-2-positive women were more likely to show evidence of maternal/fetal vascular malperfusion; however, no evidence of direct viral involvement or vertical transmission was noted by ISH and IHC.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2 infection", "locations": [{"offset": 202, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 302, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 335, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 409, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 507, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 527, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 727, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 864, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 884, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 939, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 959, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1189, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1314, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 1334, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013927", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "subchorionic thrombi", "locations": [{"offset": 1410, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1461, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 1481, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "40", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1621, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "41", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 1641, "length": 5}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692408, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "species@2697049", "disease@MESH:D013927"], "journal": "Histopathology", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Smithgall MC", "Liu-Jarin X", "Hamele-Bena D", "Cimic A", "Mourad M", "Debelenko L", "Chen X"]}
{"_id": "32692406|None", "id": "32692406", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Med. Virol.; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.1002/jmv.26321", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Kanwugu ON, Adadi P, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "HIV/SARS-CoV-2 coinfection: a global perspective.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D015658", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "HIV", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 4, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 50, "text": "Since its first appearance in Wuhan, China, SARS-CoV-2 has rapidly spread throughout the world and has become a global pandemic. Several medical comorbidities have been identified as risk factors for COVID-19. However, it remains unclear whether people with people living with HIV (PLWH) are at an increased risk of COVID-19 and severe disease manifestation, with controversial suggestion that HIV-infected individuals could be protected from severe COVID-19 by means of antiretroviral therapy (ART) or HIV-related immunosuppression. Several cases of coinfection with HIV and SARS-CoV-2 have been reported from different parts of the globe. This review seeks to provide a holistic overview of SARS-CoV-2 infection in PLWH. This article is protected by copyright. All rights reserved.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 94, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 250, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "people", "locations": [{"offset": 296, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Specie