{"_id": "32692306|None", "id": "32692306", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Biomol. Struct. Dyn.; 2020 Jul 21 1-11. doi:10.1080/07391102.2020.1794974", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Rahman MM, Saha T, Islam KJ, Suman RH, Biswas S, Rahat EU, Hossen MR, Islam R, Hossain MN, Mamun AA, Khan M, Ali MA, Halim MA, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Virtual screening, molecular dynamics and structure-activity relationship studies to identify potent approved drugs for Covid-19 treatment.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 120, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 140, "text": "Computer-aided drug screening by molecular docking, molecular dynamics (MD) and structural-activity relationship (SAR) can offer an efficient approach to identify promising drug repurposing candidates for COVID-19 treatment. In this study, computational screening is performed by molecular docking of 1615 Food and Drug Administration (FDA) approved drugs against the main protease (Mpro) of SARS-CoV-2. Several promising approved drugs, including Simeprevir, Ergotamine, Bromocriptine and Tadalafil, stand out as the best candidates based on their binding energy, fitting score and noncovalent interactions at the binding sites of the receptor. All selected drugs interact with the key active site residues, including His41 and Cys145. Various noncovalent interactions including hydrogen bonding, hydrophobic interactions, pi-sulfur and pi-pi interactions appear to be dominant in drug-Mpro complexes. MD simulations are applied for the most promising drugs. Structural stability and compactness are observed for the drug-Mpro complexes. The protein shows low flexibility in both apo and holo form during MD simulations. The MM/PBSA binding free energies are also measured for the selected drugs. For pattern recognition, structural similarity and binding energy prediction, multiple linear regression (MLR) models are used for the quantitative structural-activity relationship. The binding energy predicted by MLR model shows an 82% accuracy with the binding energy determined by molecular docking. Our details results can facilitate rational drug design targeting the SARS-CoV-2 main protease. Communicated by Ramaswamy H. Sarma.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "2698737", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SAR", "locations": [{"offset": 254, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 345, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "8673700", "type": "Gene"}, "text": "Mpro", "locations": [{"offset": 523, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 532, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D000069616", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "Simeprevir", "locations": [{"offset": 588, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D004878", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "Ergotamine", "locations": [{"offset": 600, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001971", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "Bromocriptine", "locations": [{"offset": 612, "length": 13}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D000068581", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "Tadalafil", "locations": [{"offset": 630, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "His41", "locations": [{"offset": 859, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "Cys145", "locations": [{"offset": 869, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006859", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "hydrogen", "locations": [{"offset": 920, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013455", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "sulfur", "locations": [{"offset": 967, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "8673700", "type": "Gene"}, "text": "Mpro", "locations": [{"offset": 1027, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "8673700", "type": "Gene"}, "text": "Mpro", "locations": [{"offset": 1163, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C437084", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "PBSA", "locations": [{"offset": 1269, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1711, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692306, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["chemical@MESH:D004878", "chemical@MESH:D000069616", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "species@2698737", "chemical@-", "chemical@MESH:D001971", "chemical@MESH:D000068581", "gene@8673700", "species@2697049", "chemical@MESH:D013455", "chemical@MESH:C437084", "chemical@MESH:D006859"], "journal": "J. Biomol. Struct. Dyn.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Rahman MM", "Saha T", "Islam KJ", "Suman RH", "Biswas S", "Rahat EU", "Hossen MR", "Islam R", "Hossain MN", "Mamun AA", "Khan M", "Ali MA", "Halim MA"]}
{"_id": "32692266|None", "id": "32692266", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "SLAS Discov; 2020 Jul 21 2472555220945281. doi:10.1177/2472555220945281", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Banday AH, Shameem SA, Ajaz SJ, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Potential Repurposed Therapeutics and New Vaccines against COVID-19 and Their Clinical Status.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 59, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 95, "text": "SARS-CoV-2, the virus that causes coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), was first reported in Wuhan, China, in December 2019. Since then, the virus has stretched its grip to almost all the countries in the world, affecting millions of people and causing enormous casualties. The World Health Organization (WHO) declared COVID-19 a pandemic on March 11, 2019. As of June 12, 2020, almost 7.30 million people have already been infected globally, with 413,000 reported casualties. In the United States alone, 2.06 million people have been infected and 115,000 have succumbed to this pandemic. A multipronged approach has been launched toward combating this pandemic, with the main focus on exhaustive screening, developing efficacious therapies, and vaccines for long-term immunity. Several pharmaceutical companies in collaboration with various academic institutions and governmental organizations have started investigating new therapeutics and repurposing approved drugs so as to find fast and affordable treatments against this disease. The present communication is aimed at highlighting the efforts that are currently underway to treat or prevent SARS-CoV-2 infection, with details on the science, clinical status, and timeline for selected investigational drugs and vaccines. This article is going to be of immense help to the scientific community and researchers as it brings forth all the necessary clinical information of the most-talked-about therapeutics against SARS-CoV-2. All the details pertaining to the clinical status of each therapeutic candidate have been updated as of June 12, 2020.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 95, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coronavirus disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 129, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 155, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "people", "locations": [{"offset": 329, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 414, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "people", "locations": [{"offset": 494, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infected", "locations": [{"offset": 519, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "people", "locations": [{"offset": 613, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infected", "locations": [{"offset": 630, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2 infection", "locations": [{"offset": 1243, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1565, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692266, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D007239", "species@