{"_id": "32692248|None", "id": "32692248", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Biomark Med; 2020 Jul 21 . doi:10.2217/bmm-2020-0317", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Usul E, \u015ean \u0130, Bekg\u00f6z B, \u015eahin A, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "The role of hematological parameters in COVID-19 patients in the emergency room.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 40, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 49, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 81, "text": "Aim: In this study, the roles of biomarkers from a peripheral blood sample in the diagnosis of Coronavirus Disease of 2019 (COVID-19) patients who have visited the emergency room have been evaluated. Materials & methods: Peripheral blood parameters, systemic inflammatory index (SII), neutrophil lymphocyte ratio (NLR) and platelet lymphocyte ratio were compared in patients with and without confirmed COVID-19 infection. Results: Comparisons made according to real-time PCR test results revealed that while no statistically significant difference was observed between test groups (negative-positive) regarding lymphocyte and platelet lymphocyte ratio values (p > 0.05), a statistically significant difference (p < 0.05) was found between the test groups regarding platelet, hemoglobin, leukocyte, neutrophil, NLR and SII values. Conclusion: Leukocyte, neutrophil, platelet count, NLR and SII values can be used in the diagnosis of COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "11", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Coronavirus Disease of 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 176, "length": 27}]}, {"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 205, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 215, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 447, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 483, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 492, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1013, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692248, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D007239", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "Biomark Med", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Usul E", "\u015ean \u0130", "Bekg\u00f6z B", "\u015eahin A"]}
{"_id": "32692241|None", "id": "32692241", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Ann Palliat Med; 2020 Jul 20 . doi:10.21037/apm-20-1372", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Liu M, Lyu Y, Zhao W, Yu S, Shi D, Lu W, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Case analysis of novel coronavirus pneumonia in the Second Hospital of Wuhan Iron and Steel Company, Qingshan District, Wuhan, China.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "novel coronavirus pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 17, "length": 27}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 134, "text": "BACKGROUND: To analyze the clinical and infectious characteristics of new coronavirus pneumonia with diagnosed and suspected cases in the Second Hospital of WISCO(Wuhan Iron and Steel Company) of Qingshan District, Wuhan City, and further enhance the understanding of new coronavirus pneumonia. METHODS: According to the fifth and sixth editions of the new coronavirus pneumonia diagnosis and treatment plan issued by the National Health Commission of the People's Republic of China and National Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine, we carried out the case analysis and infectious disease investigation and research on the confirmed and suspected cases of new coronavirus pneumonia admitted to the second-floor ward of the hospital from January 28th, 2020, to February 26th, 2020. RESULTS: From January 28th, 2020 to February 26th, 2020, 83 patients were admitted, 40 were cured, and 7 died. Before February 13th, 69 patients were admitted, including 22 confirmed patients and 47 suspected patients. After February 13th, the data of newly hospitalized suspected patients decreased to 2 people. The average time from onset to diagnosis was 5.38 days. About 57.1% of the confirmed patients were isolated at home before admission, and 53.2% of the suspected patients were isolated by hospital observation before admission. The proportion of fever and other clinical symptoms was 81.8%, 65.5% of the patients had the fastest heart rate of 90-120 rpm, and 11 of the patients had severe/critical illness, accounting for 20%. The count of leukocytes, neutrophils, and C-reactive proteins (CRPs) in severe patients was higher than those in light patients (P<0.05), and the count of lymphocytes was lower than that in mild patients (P=0.016). CONCLUSIONS: The novel coronavirus pneumonia in Qingshan District of Wuhan in February was diagnosed promptly, controlled,and treated effectively. The combination of traditional Chinese and western medicine in the treatment of new coronavirus pneumonia might help patients.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "new coronavirus pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 204, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "new coronavirus pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 402, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "new coronavirus pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 487, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "People", "locations": [{"offset": 590, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003141", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infectious disease", "locations": [{"offset": 715, "length": 18}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "new coronavirus pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 801, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 986, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1062, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1109, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1135, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1207, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "people", "locations": [{"offset": 1231, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1324, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1400, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D005334", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "fever", "locations": [{"offset": 1483, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "40", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1541, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "41", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1606, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "42", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1743, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "43", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1783, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "44", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1859, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "45", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "novel coronavirus pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 1896, "length": 27}]}, {"id": "46", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "new coronavirus pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 2106, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "47", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 2143, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32692241, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D005334", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:D003141", "disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "Ann Palliat Med", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Liu M", "Lyu Y", "Zhao W", "Yu S", "Shi D", "Lu W"]}
{"_id": "32692238|None", "id": "32692238", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Ann Palliat Med; 2020 Jul 19 . doi:10.21037/apm-20-1330", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Liang K, Huang X, Chen H, Qiu L, Zhuang Y, Zou C, Bai Y, Huang Y, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Tongue diagnosis and treatment in traditional Chinese medicine for severe COVID-19: a case report.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 74, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 99, "text": "As one of the most urgent public health events, coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) has attracted worldwide attention. This case highlighted the importance of close coordination between Chinese medicine and western medicine in the diagnosis and treatment, as well as the need for rapid dissemination of clinical information related to patient care with this emerging infection. We reported a COVID-19 case confirmed in China and described the identification, diagnosis, clinical course, and management of the case. The patient had initial mild symptoms at presentation; it progressed to severe pneumonia on the 10th day of onset. This cured case supplied a time series analysis of tongue characteristics found in severe COVID-19. Chinese medicine formulae were tweaked by tongue characteristics, which include tongue color, fur thickness, and fur color. Tongue images were obtained every two days, and the changes were firmly related to the progression of COVID-19. These tongue characteristics could be used as effective, non-intrusive indices for the distinct stages of COVID-19 stages. Our study was the first time tongue diagnosis was applied in time series analysis of the progression of COVID-19 disease. We found that tongue color, fur thickness, and fur color were closely related to the progression of COVID-19 by analyzing various tongue images obtained regularly. Based on this success, we will further apply tongue diagnosis to tongue characteristics of COVID-19 patients to help limit the risk of COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coronavirus disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 147, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 173, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 434, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 466, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 491, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 618, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D011014", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 693, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 819, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1055, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1171, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1292, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1410, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245