{"_id": "32691655|None", "id": "32691655", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Scand J Urol; 2020 Jul 21 1-2. doi:10.1080/21681805.2020.1794956", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Mostafid H, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Cystoscopic surveillance for bladder cancer: Learning the lessons forced upon us by the Covid-19 pandemic.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001749", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "bladder cancer", "locations": [{"offset": 29, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Covid-19", "locations": [{"offset": 88, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 107, "text": "", "sentences": [], "annotations": [], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32691655, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D001749", "disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "Scand J Urol", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Mostafid H"]}
{"_id": "32691645|None", "id": "32691645", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J Dermatolog Treat; 2020 Jul 21 1-11. doi:10.1080/09546634.2020.1799918", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Ghalamkarpour F, Pourani MR, Abdollahimajd F, Zargari O, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "A case of severe psoriatic erythroderma with COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003873", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "psoriatic erythroderma", "locations": [{"offset": 17, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 45, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 55, "text": "COVID-19 caused by the SARS-CoV-2, became pandemic very quickly. Management of severe dermatologic disorders in patients who require systemic immunosuppressive treatment is a major concern in COVID-19 pandemic era. Here we report a 45-year-old homeless addicted male with second flare of severe psoriatic erythroderma and positive PCR test for COVID 19. His first attack occurred two months earlier, when he was treated and relatively controlled with cyclosporine. He discontinued all his treatment after discharged. At the time of his first admission he had been screened for COVID 19; however, all examination were negative.During this period, he not only became SARS-CoV-2 positive but also discontinued his medication. It seems that both factors could be important in flare of his erythroderma.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 55, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 78, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D000168", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "dermatologic disorders", "locations": [{"offset": 141, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 167, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 247, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003873", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "psoriatic erythroderma", "locations": [{"offset": 350, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID 19", "locations": [{"offset": 399, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D016572", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "cyclosporine", "locations": [{"offset": 506, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID 19", "locations": [{"offset": 632, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 720, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32691645, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D000168", "species@2697049", "chemical@MESH:D016572", "disease@MESH:D003873"], "journal": "J Dermatolog Treat", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Ghalamkarpour F", "Pourani MR", "Abdollahimajd F", "Zargari O"]}
{"_id": "32691641|None", "id": "32691641", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Matern. Fetal. Neonatal. Med.; 2020 Jul 21 1-22. doi:10.1080/14767058.2020.1798398", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Yassa M, Yirmibes C, Cavusoglu G, Eksi H, Dogu C, Usta C, Mutlu MA, Birol P, Gulumser C, Tug N, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Outcomes of universal SARS-CoV-2 testing program in pregnant women admitted to hospital and the adjuvant role of lung ultrasound in screening: A prospective cohort study.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 22, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 61, "length": 5}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 171, "text": "Background: The emerging evidence for the asymptomatic carriers of SARS-CoV-2 infection emphasized the critical need for universal screening of pregnant women.Objectives: This study aimed to present the prevalence of overall and asymptomatic SARS-CoV-2 infection rates in pregnant women admitted to the hospital, and assess the diagnostic accuracy of maternal symptoms and lung ultrasound (LUS) findings in detecting the infection.Patients and methods: This prospective cohort study was conducted at a single tertiary centre in Istanbul, Turkey, for a month period starting from 27th April, 2020. Women with a confirmed pregnancy regardless of the gestational week admitted to the obstetric unit with any indication were consecutively underwent LUS and PCR testing for SARS-CoV-2.Results: A total of 296 patients were included for the final analysis. The universal screening strategy diagnosed 23 pregnant women (7.77%) with SARS-CoV-2 infection. The rate of symptomatic and asymptomatic patients diagnosed with SARS-CoV-2 was found as 3.72% (n = 11) and 4.05% (n = 12), respectively. Four of nine women who underwent a second testing for SARS-CoV-2 upon abnormal LUS findings were found positive eventually (17.4%, n = 4/23). The asymptomatic pregnant women with LUS score of 1 and those with normal LUS findings were considered as likely to be normal. Symptomatic patients with LUS score of 1 and those with score of 2 or 3 were considered as abnormal. On a secondary diagnostic performance analysis, the positive predictive value and the sensitivity were found as 44% and 47.8% for the triage based on maternal symptoms and, 82.3% and 60.9% for the triage based on LUS, respectively.Conclusion: A one-month trial period of universal testing for SARS-CoV-2 infection with RT-PCR in pregnant women who admitted to the hospital showed an overall and asymptomatic infection diagnose rate of 7.77% and 4%, respectively. Using lung ultrasound was found more predictive in detecting the infection than the use of symptomatology solely.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2 infection", "locations": [{"offset": 238, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 324, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2 infection", "locations": [{"offset": 413, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "women", "locations": [{"offset": 452, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 592, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Patients", "locations": [{"offset": 602, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "9103", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Turkey", "locations": [{"offset": 709, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": 