{"_id": "32691000|None", "id": "32691000", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Integr Med Res; 2020 Sep ; 9 (3) 100465. doi:10.1016/j.imr.2020.100465", "year": "2020", "article-id_pmc": "PMC7328533", "type": "title", "authors": "Ang L, Lee HW, Kim A, Lee MS, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Herbal medicine for the management of COVID-19 during the medical observation period: A review of guidelines.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "1407750", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Herbal medicine", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 38, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 110, "text": "Background: Medical observation period is a period of 14 days after any exposure to coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) occurred. This review aimed to summarize and analyze the herbs and herbal formulae recommended by available guidelines. Methods: A total of 14 sources were searched for potential guidelines that provide herbal medicine treatment for the medical observation period of COVID-19. We summarized and analyzed the recommended herbal formulae and performed a network analysis to identify the relationship between herbs. Results: We found 9 guidelines that provide herbal formula for medical observation based on clinical manifestation. There are 12 herbal formulae with a total of 53 herbs recommended by the guidelines. The result of our network analysis showed that the herb Citri Reticulatae Pericarpium (Chen Pi) strongly paired with the herb Glycyrrhizae Radix et Rhizoma (Gan Cao). Conclusion: This review briefly summarized the usage of herbal medicine for the medical observation period of COVID-19 and may serve as a reference for future studies. More research is needed in the future to provide evidence on the usage of herbal medicine in various phases of COVID-10.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coronavirus disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 194, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 220, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "1407750", "type": "Species"}, "text": "herbal medicine", "locations": [{"offset": 433, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 497, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "1407750", "type": "Species"}, "text": "herbal medicine", "locations": [{"offset": 1067, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1121, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "1407750", "type": "Species"}, "text": "herbal medicine", "locations": [{"offset": 1253, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID", "locations": [{"offset": 1290, "length": 5}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32691000, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@1407750", "disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "Integr Med Res", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Ang L", "Lee HW", "Kim A", "Lee MS"]}
{"_id": "32690999|None", "id": "32690999", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Integr Med Res; 2020 Sep ; 9 (3) 100457. doi:10.1016/j.imr.2020.100457", "year": "2020", "article-id_pmc": "PMC7308745", "type": "title", "authors": "Hunter J, Arentz S, Goldenberg J, Yang G, Beardsley J, Mertz D, Leeder S, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Rapid review protocol: Zinc for the prevention or treatment of COVID-19 and other coronavirus-related respiratory tract infections.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 63, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "11118", "type": "Species"}, "text": "coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 82, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012141", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "respiratory tract infections", "locations": [{"offset": 102, "length": 28}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 132, "text": "Background: The global COVID-19 pandemic has prompted an urgent search for effective interventions. SARS-CoV-2 mortality/morbidity risk increases with age and for those chronic disease co-morbidities, both of which are associated with lower zinc status, as is the risk of infection. Methods: Rapid review methods will be applied to a systematic review of zinc for the prevention or treatment of SARS-CoV-2 and viral respiratory tract infections in humans. Included are published studies reporting randomised and quasi-randomised controlled trials that compare zinc intervention to placebo and/or other comparator interventions. English and Chinese language databases will be searched for primary studies of viral respiratory tract infections and clinical trial registries for SARS-CoV-2 infections. Due to concerns about indirectness, studies evaluating non-SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus infections will be rated down by one level, and non-specific or confirmed non-coronavirus viral infections will be rated down by two levels. Review constraints include (1) using Google translate when screening articles published in languages other than English or Chinese and limited translation (2) following calibration, only one reviewer will screen articles, extract data, appraise quality and conduct the analysis, (3) prioritising data extraction and meta-analyses of SARS-CoV-2 studies and critical outcomes of other viral infections, followed by high risk groups and (4) reporting important preliminary findings prior to peer review if necessary. Discussion: The application of these rapid review methods and broadening the inclusion criteria to include other coronavirus-related viral respiratory tract infections aims to enable a timely evidence appraisal of priority research questions and dissemination of results. Study registration: PROSPERO CRD42020182044.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 155, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 232, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 404, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 527, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012141", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "respiratory tract infections", "locations": [{"offset": 548, "length": 28}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "humans", "locations": [{"offset": 580, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": null, "type": "Disease", "db": null}, "text": "viral respiratory tract infections", "locations": [{"offset": 839, "length": 34}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2 infections", "locations": [{"offset": 908, "length": 21}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 990, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D018352", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coronavirus infections", "locations": [{"offset": 1001, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "11118", "type": "Species"}, "text": "coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 1091, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001102", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "viral infections", "locations": [{"offset": 1103, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1487, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001102", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "viral infections", "locations": [{"offset": 1537, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "11118", "type": "Species"}, "text": "coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 1781, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012141", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "respiratory tract infections", "locations": [{"offset": 1807, "length": 28}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32690999, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D018352", "disease@MESH:D012141", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "species@9606", "species@2697049", "disease@MESH:D001102", "disease@MESH:D007239", "species@11118"], "journal": "Integr Med Res", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Hunter J", "Arentz S", "Goldenberg J", "Yang G", "Beardsley J", "Mertz D", "Leeder S"]}
{"_id": "32690998|None", "id": "32690998", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Respir Med Case Rep; 2020 ; 31 101154. doi:10.1016/j.rmcr.2020.101154", "year": "2020", "article-id_pmc": "PMC7348611", "type": "title", "authors": "Galo J, Celli D, Gross D, Holt G, Campos M, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "A presentation of E-Cigarette vaping associated lung injury (EVALI) caused by THC-Containing electronic smoking device.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055370", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "lung injury", "locations": [{"offset": 48, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013759", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "THC", "locations": [{"offset": 78, "length": 3}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 120, "text": "Several cases have recently been reported concerning the development of a syndrome of acute lung injury associated with the use of electronic cigarettes, leading to respiratory failure and several deaths. We present a case of a young veteran who presented with e-cigarette vaping associated lung injury (EVALI) to a primary care clinic and who required subsequent inpatient admission and home oxygen therapy after discharge. The patient afterwards improved after a three-month course of steroids and cessation of THC-containing electronic cigarettes, consistent with previously reported cases. Furthermore, evidence on bronchoscopy and biopsy demonstrated intracellular lipid droplets in the patient's macrophages. This outpatient case of EVALI prompts primary care providers to raise suspicion of this condition, and enquire about the use of e-cigarettes, particularly THC-containing vaping products. Furthermore, in the setting of the COVID-19 pandemic, similar clinical and radiographic presentations between COVID-19 and EVALI can be seen.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055371", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "acute lung injury", "locations": [{"offset": 206, "length": 17}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012131", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "respiratory failure", "locations": [{"offset": 285, "length": 19}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "deaths", "locations": [{"offset": 317, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055370", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "lung injury", "locations": [{"offset": 411, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D010100", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "oxygen", "locations": [{"offset": 513, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 549, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013256", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "steroids", "locations": [{"offset": 607, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013759", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "THC", "locations": [{"offset": 633, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008055", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "lipid", "locations": [{"offset": 790, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 812, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "outpatient", "locations": [{"offset": 840, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013759", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "THC", "locations": [{"offset": 990, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1057, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1132, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32690998, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["chemical@MESH:D010100", "chemical@MESH:D013759", "disease@MESH:D003643", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:D012131", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D055371", "disease@MESH:D055370", "chemical@MESH:D008055", "chemical@MESH:D013256"], "journal": "Respir Med Case Rep", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Galo J", "Celli D", "Gross D", "Holt G", "Campos M"]}
{"_id": "32690997|None", "id": "32690997", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Adv Simul (Lond); 2020 ; 5 13. doi:10.1186/s41077-020-00131-3", "year": "2020", "article-id_pmc": "PMC7363498", "type": "title", "authors": "Ingrassia PL, Capogna G, Diaz-Navarro C, Szyld D, Tomola S, Leon-Castelao E, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "COVID-19 crisis, safe reopening of simulation centres and the new normal: food for thought.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 92, "text": "Background: The world is facing a massive burden from the coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) pandemic. Governments took the extraordinary step of locking down their own countries to curb the spread of the coronavirus. After weeks of severe restrictions, countries have begun to relax their strict lockdown measures. However, reopening will not be back to normal.Simulation facilities (SF) are training spaces that enable health professionals and students to learn skills and procedures in a safe and protected environment. Today's clinicians and students have an expectation that simulation laboratories are part of lifelong healthcare education. There is great uncertainty about how COVID-19 will impact future training in SF. In particular, the delivery of training activities will benefit of adequate safety measures implemented for all individuals involved.This paper discusses how to safely reopen SF in the post-lockdown phase. Main body: The paper outlines 10 focus points and provides operational tips and recommendations consistent with current international guidelines to reopen SF safely in the post-lockdown phase. Considering a variety of national advices and regulations which describe initial measures for the reopening of workplaces as well as international public health recommendations, we provide points of reflection that can guide decision-makers and SF leaders on how to develop local approaches to specific challenges. The tips have been laid out taking also into account two main factors: (a) the SF audience, mainly consisting of undergraduate and postgraduate healthcare professionals, who might face exposure to COVID-19 infection, and (b) for many simulation-based activities, such as teamwork training, adequate physical distancing cannot be maintained. Conclusions: The planning of future activities will have to be based not only on safety but also on flexibility principles.Sharing common methods consistent with national and international health guidelines, while taking into account the specific characteristics of the different contexts and centres, will ultimately foster dissemination of good practices.This article seeks to further the conversation. It is our hope that this manuscript will prompt research about the impact of such mitigation procedures and measures in different countries.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "8", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "coronavirus disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 150, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "9", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 176, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "10", "infons": {"identifier": "11118", "type": "Species"}, "text": "coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 298, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "11", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 777, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1732, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 1741, "length": 9}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 