{"_id": "32690991|None", "id": "32690991", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Ann Med Surg (Lond); 2020 Sep ; 57 14-16. doi:10.1016/j.amsu.2020.06.038", "year": "2020", "article-id_pmc": "PMC7351662", "type": "title", "authors": "Al-Zoubi NA, Obeidat BR, Al-Ghazo MA, Hayajneh WA, Alomari AH, Mazahreh TS, Al-Faouri IG, Obeidat K, Issa AB, Aleshawi A, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Prevalence of positive COVID-19 among asymptomatic health care workers who care patients infected with the novel coronavirus: A retrospective study.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 23, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 80, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infected", "locations": [{"offset": 89, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "novel coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 107, "length": 17}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 149, "text": "Background: Limited information is available about COVID-19 infections among health care workers. Sensitive detection of COVID-19 cases in health care workers is crucial for hospital infection prevention policy, particularly for those who work with vulnerable patients. The aim of this study is to describe the prevalence of positive COVID-19 among asymptomatic health care workers who took care of patients with COVID-19 during the pandemic. Methods: This retrospective study included all health care workers at King Abdullah University Hospital who take care of patients infected with COVID-19 patients from March 18, 2020 to April 29, 2020. They were tested for COVID-19 infection by use of real-time reverse-transcriptase rRT-PCR on samples from nasopharyngeal swabs. Results: A total number of 370 health care workers were screened. The majority were nurses followed by physicians and other personnel. This study showed that all asymptomatic health care workers were tested negative for COVID-19Q. Conclusion: Unexpectedly, the prevalence of positive COVID-19 among asymptomatic health care workers who take care of patients infected with the novel coronavirus was 0%. This result must be cautiously interpreted. Further studies are needed in order to find effective strategy of screening health care workers to insure a safe working environment.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 200, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infections", "locations": [{"offset": 209, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 270, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 332, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 409, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 483, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 548, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 562, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 713, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infected", "locations": [{"o