{"_id": "32690880|None", "id": "32690880", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Leukemia; 2020 Jul 20 . doi:10.1038/s41375-020-0986-7", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Li Q, Chen L, Li Q, He W, Yu J, Chen L, Cao Y, Chen W, Di WuDong F, Cai L, Ran Q, Li L, Liu Q, Ren W, Gao F, Wang H, Chen Z, Gale RP, Hu Y, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Cancer increases risk of in-hospital death from COVID-19 in persons <65 years and those not in complete remission.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Cancer", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "death", "locations": [{"offset": 37, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 48, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "persons", "locations": [{"offset": 60, "length": 7}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 115, "text": "The impact of cancer on outcome of persons with coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) after infection with acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus-2 (SARS-CoV-2) is controversial. We studied 1859 subjects with COVID-19 from seven centers in Wuhan, China, 65 of whom had cancer. We found having cancer was an independent risk factor for in-hospital death from COVID-19 in persons <65 years (hazard ratio [HR] = 2.45, 95% confidence interval [CI], 1.04, 5.76; P = 0.041) but not in those >=65 years (HR = 1.12 [0.56, 2.24]; P = 0.740). It was also more common in those not in complete remission. Risks of in-hospital death were similar in subjects with solid cancers and those with hematological cancers. These data may help predict outcomes of persons with cancer and COVID-19.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "27", "infons"