"}, "text": "tocilizumab", "locations": [{"offset": 1653, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "56", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1676, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "57", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003643", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "mortality", "locations": [{"offset": 1699, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "58", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C502936", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "TCZ", "locations": [{"offset": 1716, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "59", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C502936", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "TCZ", "locations": [{"offset": 1805, "length": 3}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32690352, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["chemical@MESH:C502936", "disease@MESH:D006973", "disease@MESH:D009765", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D003643", "disease@MESH:D003920"], "journal": "J. Autoimmun.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Moreno-P\u00e9rez O", "Andres M", "Leon-Ramirez JM", "S\u00e1nchez-Pay\u00e1 J", "Rodr\u00edguez JC", "S\u00e1nchez R", "Garc\u00eda-Sevila R", "Boix V", "Gil J", "Merino E"]}
{"_id": "32690337|None", "id": "32690337", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Curr Probl Diagn Radiol; 2020 Jun 29 . doi:10.1067/j.cpradiol.2020.06.012", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Hoegger MJ, Shetty AS, Denner DR, Gould JE, Wahl RL, Raptis CA, Ballard DH, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "A Snapshot of Radiology Training During the Early COVID-19 Pandemic.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 50, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 69, "text": "PURPOSE: The COVID-19 pandemic transformed the personal and professional lives of radiology trainees. The purpose of this study was to broadly summarize the impact of COVID-19 on radiology trainees and their training programs via data collected during the early pandemic. MATERIALS AND METHODS: An online survey was distributed to radiology chief residents in residencies throughout North America with responses collected between March 20th, 2020 and May 15th, 2020, which coincided with the development of initial COVID-19 peaks in North America. A subset of COVID-19 pandemic questions included resident wellness, imaging opinions, residency infrastructure change, and opinions regarding the Core Exam delay. RESULTS: One hundred forty chief residents from 86 institutions responded to COVID-19-related questions. Nearly all responding programs (99%; 85/86) reported institutional positive cases of COVID-19. Most residents (94%; 132/140) thought laboratory testing provided more value than imaging. Fifty-seven percent of respondents (80/140) would use COVID-19-related terminology when encountering chest CT findings supportive of viral pneumonia in symptomatic patients. There was little reported change in the number of residents on call (no change reported in >80% of programs). Fifty-nine percent of residents (83/140) reported increased stress related to the COVID-19 pandemic. The majority of programs (93%) had fewer residents on service (80/86 responding programs). CONCLUSIONS: COVID-19 dramatically affected radiology residencies during the early pandemic period. As we enter future phases of the COVID-19 pandemic, careful thought should also be given to rebuilding the radiology resident experience.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 82, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 236, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 584, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 629, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 857, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 970, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1125, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": null, "type": "Disease", "db": null}, "text": "viral pneumonia", "locations": [{"offset": 1204, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 1235, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1437, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1560, "length": 8}