{"_id": "32690029|None", "id": "32690029", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Cardiovasc Diabetol; 2020 Jul 20 ; 19 (1) 114. doi:10.1186/s12933-020-01089-2", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Ceriello A, Standl E, Catrinoiu D, Itzhak B, Lalic NM, Rahelic D, Schnell O, \u0160krha J, Valensi P, \u201cDiabetes and Cardiovascular Disease (D&amp;CVD)\u201d Study Group of the European Association for the Study of Diabetes (EASD), ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Issues for the management of people with diabetes and COVID-19 in ICU.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "people", "locations": [{"offset": 29, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003920", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "diabetes", "locations": [{"offset": 41, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 54, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 71, "text": "In the pandemic \"Corona Virus Disease 2019\" (COVID-19) people with diabetes have a high risk to require ICU admission. The management of diabetes in Intensive Care Unit is always challenging, however, when diabetes is present in COVID-19 the situation seems even more complicated. An optimal glycemic control, avoiding acute hyperglycemia, hypoglycemia and glycemic variability may significantly improve the outcome. In this case, intravenous insulin infusion with continuous glucose monitoring should be the choice. No evidence suggests stopping angiotensin-converting-enzyme inhibitors, angiotensin-renin-blockers or statins, even it has been suggested that they may increase the expression of Angiotensin-Converting-Enzyme-2 (ACE2) receptor, which is used by \"Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) to penetrate into the cells. A real issue is the usefulness of several biomarkers, which have been suggested to be measured during the COVID-19. N-Terminal-pro-Brain Natriuretic-Peptide, D-dimer and hs-Troponin are often increased in diabetes. Their meaning in the case of diabetes and COVID-19 should be therefore very carefully evaluated. Even though we understand that in such a critical situation some of these requests are not so easy to implement, we believe that the best possible action to prevent a worse outcome is essential in any medical act.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Corona Virus Disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 88, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 116, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "people", "locations": [{"offset": 126, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003920", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "diabetes", "locations": [{"offset": 138, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003920", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "diabetes", "locations": [{"offset": 208, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003920", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "diabetes", "locations": [{"offset": 277, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 300, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006943", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "acute hyperglycemia", "locations": [{"offset": 390, "length": 19}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007003", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "hypoglycemia", "locations": [{"offset": 411, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "3630", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "173"}, "text": "insulin", "locations": [{"offset": 514, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D005947", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "glucose", "locations": [{"offset": 547, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "1636", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "37351"}, "text": "angiotensin-converting-enzyme", "locations": [{"offset": 618, "length": 29}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "59272", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "41448"}, "text": "Angiotensin-Converting-Enzyme-2", "locations": [{"offset": 767, "length": 31}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "59272", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "41448"}, "text": "ACE2", "locations": [{"offset": 800, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "40", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2", "locations": [{"offset": 834, "length": 47}]}, {"id": "41", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 883, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "42", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1030, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "43", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003920", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "diabetes", "locations": [{"offset": 1129, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "44", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003920", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "diabetes", "locations": [{"offset": 1168, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "45", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 1181, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32690029, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:C000657245", "disease@MESH:D007003", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:D003920", "gene@59272", "chemical@MESH:D005947", "gene@1636", "species@2697049", "disease@MESH:D006943", "gene@3630"], "journal": "Cardiovasc Diabetol", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Ceriello A", "Standl E", "Catrinoiu D", "Itzhak B", "Lalic NM", "Rahelic D", "Schnell O", "\u0160krha J", "Valensi P", "\u201cDiabetes and Cardiovascular Disease (D&amp;CVD)\u201d Study Group of the European Association for the Study of Diabetes (EASD)"]}
{"_id": "32689956|None", "id": "32689956", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "BMC Infect. Dis.; 2020 Jul 20 ; 20 (1) 526. doi:10.1186/s12879-020-05251-9", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Wang X, Pan Y, Zhang D, Chen L, Jia L, Li X, Yang P, Wang Q, Macintyre CR, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Basic epidemiological parameter values from data of real-world in mega-cities: the characteristics of COVID-19 in Beijing, China.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 102, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 130, "text": "BACKGROUND: With the spread of SARS-CoV-2 worldwide, understanding the basic epidemiological parameter values of COVID-19 from real-world data in mega-cities is essential for disease prevention and control. METHODS: To investigate the epidemiological parameters in SARS-CoV-2 infected cases in Beijing, we studied all confirmed cases and close contacts in Beijing from Jan 1st to Apr 3rd 2020. The epidemiological and virological characteristics of SARS-CoV-2 were analyzed. RESULTS: A total of 602 cases were positive for SARS-CoV-2, including 585 confirmed patients and 17 asymptomatic infections. The imported cases were mainly from Wuhan initially and then from abroad. Among 585 confirmed case-patients, the median age was 39 years old. The mean incubation period was 6.3 days. The secondary attack rate among households was higher than social contacts (15.6 vs 4.6%). The secondary attack rate of healthcare workers (HCWs) was higher than non-HCWs' (7.3 vs 4.2%). The basic reproduction number was 2.0, and the average serial interval was 7.6 days. No significant genetic variant was identified. CONCLUSIONS: The transmissibility of SARS-CoV-2 was relatively high, especially among households and from HCWs, which draws specific public health attention. So far, no evidence of widespread circulation of SARS-CoV-2 in communities in Beijing was found.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 161, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 243, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2 infected", "locations": [{"offset": 395, "length": 19}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "5366", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "88883"}, "text": "Apr", "locations": [{"offset": 510, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 579, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 653, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 689, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infections", "locations": [{"offset": 718, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 829, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1269, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 1439, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32689956, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "gene@5366", "species@2697049", "disease@MESH:D007239"], "journal": "BMC Infect. Dis.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Wang X", "Pan Y", "Zhang D", "Chen L