{"_id": "32689701|None", "id": "32689701", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Thorac. Cardiovasc. Surg.; 2020 Aug ; 160 (2) 452-455. doi:10.1016/j.jtcvs.2020.04.011", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Haft JW, Atluri P, Ailawadi G, Engelman DT, Grant MC, Hassan A, Legare JF, Whitman GJR, Arora RC, Society of Thoracic Surgeons COVID-19 Task Force and the Workforce for Adult Cardiac and Vascular Surgery, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Adult cardiac surgery during the COVID-19 pandemic: A tiered patient triage guidance statement.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 33, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 61, "length": 7}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 96, "text": "In the setting of the current novel coronavirus pandemic, this document has been generated to provide guiding statements for the adult cardiac surgeon to consider in a rapidly evolving national landscape. Acknowledging the risk for a potentially prolonged need for cardiac surgery procedure deferral, we have created this proposed template for physicians and interdisciplinary teams to consider in protecting their patients, institution, and their highly specialized cardiac surgery team. In addition, recommendations on the transition from traditional in-person patient assessments and outpatient follow-up are provided. Lastly, we advocate that cardiac surgeons must continue to serve as leaders, experts, and relevant members of our medical community, shifting our role as necessary in this time of need.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "8", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "novel coronavirus", "locations": [{"offset": 126, "length": 17}]}, {"id": "9", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 511, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "10", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 659, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "11", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "outpatient", "locations": [{"offset": 683, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32689701, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245", "species@2697049"], "journal": "J. Thorac. Cardiovasc. Surg.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Haft JW", "Atluri P", "Ailawadi G", "Engelman DT", "Grant MC", "Hassan A", "Legare JF", "Whitman GJR", "Arora RC", "Society of Thoracic Surgeons COVID-19 Task Force and the Workforce for Adult Cardiac and Vascular Surgery"]}
{"_id": "32689700|None", "id": "32689700", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Thorac. Cardiovasc. Surg.; 2020 Aug ; 160 (2) 447-451. doi:10.1016/j.jtcvs.2020.04.059", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Engelman DT, Lother S, George I, Funk DJ, Ailawadi G, Atluri P, Grant MC, Haft JW, Hassan A, Legare JF, Whitman GJR, Arora RC, Society of Thoracic Surgeons COVID-19 Task Force, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Adult cardiac surgery and the COVID-19 pandemic: Aggressive infection mitigation strategies are necessary in the operating room and surgical recovery.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 30, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Aggressive infection", "locations": [{"offset": 49, "length": 20}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 151, "text": "The COVID-19 pandemic necessitates aggressive infection mitigation strategies to reduce the risk to patients and healthcare providers. This document is intended to provide a framework for the adult cardiac surgeon to consider in this rapidly changing environment. Preoperative, intraoperative, and postoperative detailed protective measures are outlined. These are guidance recommendations during a pandemic surge to be used for all patients while local COVID-19 disease burden remains elevated.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "9", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 155, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "10", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "aggressive infection", "locations": [{"offset": 186, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "11", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 251, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 584, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 605, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32689700, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D007239", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "J. Thorac. Cardiovasc. Surg.", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Engelman DT", "Lother S", "George I", "Funk DJ", "Ailawadi G", "Atluri P", "Grant MC", "Haft JW", "Hassan A", "Legare JF", "Whitman GJR", "Arora RC", "Society of Thoracic Surgeons COVID-19 Task Force"]}
{"_id": "32689650|None", "id": "32689650", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J Stroke Cerebrovasc Dis; 2020 Aug ; 29 (8) 104988. doi:10.1016/j.jstrokecerebrovasdis.2020.104988", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Desai SM, Guyette FX, Martin-Gill C, Jadhav AP, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Collateral damage - Impact of a pandemic on stroke emergency services.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 44, "length": 6}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 71, "text": "BACKGROUND: The COVID-19 pandemic's impact on stroke care is two-fold direct impact of the infection and indirect impact on non-COVID-19 diseases. Anecdotal evidence and clinical observation suggest that there is a decrease in the number of patients presenting with stroke during the pandemic. We aim to understand the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on the utilization of stroke emergency services on a single comprehensive stroke center (CSC). METHODS: We performed a retrospective analysis of a prospectively maintained database and compared all emergency department (ED) encounters, acute stroke admissions (including TIA), and thrombectomy cases admitted in March 2017-2019 to patients admitted in March 2020 at a comprehensive stroke center. RESULTS: Number of total ED encounters (22%, p=0.005), acute ischemic strokes (40%, p=0.001), and TIAs (60%, p=0.163) decreased between March of 2017-2019 compared to March of 2020. The number of patients undergoing EVT in March 2020 was comparable to March 2017-2019 (p=0.430). CONCLUSION: A pandemic-related stay-at-home policy reduces the utilization of stroke emergency services at a CSC. This effect appears to be more prominent for ED encounters, all stroke admissions and TIAs, and less impactful for severe strokes. Given the relatively low prevalence of COVID-19 cases in our region, this decrement is likely related to healthcare seeking behavior rather than capacity saturation.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 87, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 117, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 162, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 199, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 312, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 337, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 404, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 444, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 496, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "acute stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 658, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 753, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 804, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002544", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "ischemic strokes", "locations": [{"offset": 880, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier"