{"_id": "32689645|None", "id": "32689645", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J Stroke Cerebrovasc Dis; 2020 Aug ; 29 (8) 104980. doi:10.1016/j.jstrokecerebrovasdis.2020.104980", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Ford T, Curiale G, Nguyen TN, Aparicio H, Hamlyn EK, Gangadhara S, Cervantes-Arslanian AM, Greer D, Romero JR, Shulman JG, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Optimization of resources and modifications in acute ischemic stroke care in response to the global COVID-19 pandemic.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002544", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "ischemic stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 53, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 100, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 119, "text": "BACKGROUND: The COVID-19 pandemic has presented unprecedented challenges to healthcare organizations worldwide. A steadily rising number of patients requiring intensive care, a large proportion from racial and ethnic minorities, demands creative solutions to provide high-quality care while ensuring healthcare worker safety in the face of limited resources. Boston Medical Center has been particularly affected due to the underserved patient population we care for and the increased risk of ischemic stroke in patients with COVID-19 infection. METHODS: We present protocol modifications developed to manage patients with acute ischemic stroke in a safe and effective manner while prioritizing judicious use of personal protective equipment and intensive care unit resources. CONCLUSION: We feel this information will benefit other organizations facing similar obstacles in caring for the most vulnerable patient populations during this ongoing public health crisis.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 135, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 259, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 554, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002544", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "ischemic stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 611, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 630, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 644, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007239", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "infection", "locations": [{"offset": 653, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 727, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002544", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "ischemic stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 747, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 1024, "length": 7}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 32689645, "pmcid": null, "created": {"$date": 1595454010467}, "accessions": ["disease@MESH:D007239", "species@9606", "disease@MESH:D002544", "disease@MESH:C000657245"], "journal": "J Stroke Cerebrovasc Dis", "year": 2020, "authors": ["Ford T", "Curiale G", "Nguyen TN", "Aparicio H", "Hamlyn EK", "Gangadhara S", "Cervantes-Arslanian AM", "Greer D", "Romero JR", "Shulman JG"]}
{"_id": "32689643|None", "id": "32689643", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J Stroke Cerebrovasc Dis; 2020 Aug ; 29 (8) 104941. doi:10.1016/j.jstrokecerebrovasdis.2020.104941", "year": "2020", "type": "title", "authors": "Divani AA, Andalib S, Di Napoli M, Lattanzi S, Hussain MS, Biller J, McCullough LD, Azarpazhooh MR, Seletska A, Mayer SA, Torbey M, ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Coronavirus Disease 2019 and Stroke: Clinical Manifestations and Pathophysiological Insights.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Coronavirus Disease 2019 and Stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 35}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 94, "text": "Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), caused by the severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2), is a global health threat. Some COVID-19 patients have exhibited widespread neurological manifestations including stroke. Acute ischemic stroke, intracerebral hemorrhage, and cerebral venous sinus thrombosis have been reported in patients with COVID-19. COVID-19-associated coagulopathy is increasingly recognized as a result of acute infection and is likely caused by inflammation, including inflammatory cytokine storm. Recent studies suggest that axonal transport of SARS-CoV-2 to the brain can occur via the cribriform plate adjacent to the olfactory bulb that may lead to symptomatic anosmia. The internalization of SARS-CoV-2 is mediated by the binding of the spike glycoprotein of the virus to the angiotensin-converting enzyme 2 (ACE2) on cellular membranes. ACE2 is expressed in several tissues including lung alveolar cells, gastrointestinal tissue, and brain. The aim of this review is to provide insights into the clinical manifestations and pathophysiological mechanisms of stroke in COVID-19 patients. SARS-CoV-2 can down-regulate ACE2 and, in turn, overactivate the classical renin-angiotensin system (RAS) axis and decrease the activation of the alternative RAS pathway in the brain. The consequent imbalance in vasodilation, neuroinflammation, oxidative stress, and thrombotic response may contribute to the pathophysiology of stroke during SARS-CoV-2 infection.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Coronavirus disease 2019", "locations": [{"offset": 94, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 120, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2", "locations": [{"offset": 145, "length": 47}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "2697049", "type": "Species"}, "text": "SARS-CoV-2", "locations": [{"offset": 194, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C000657245", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "COVID-19", "locations": [{"offset": 239, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 248, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020521", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 321, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002544", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "ischemic stroke", "locations": [{"offset": 335, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "40", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002543", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "intracerebral hemorrhage", "locations": [{"offset": 352, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "41", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012851", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "cerebral venous sinus thrombosis", "locations": [{"offset": 382, "length": 32}]}, {"id": "42", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 437, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "43", "infons": {"iden